<node id="2011 Metric">
  <data key="d0">2011 Metric</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The 2011 Metric represents a set of performance measurements recorded across eight leading North American research institutions during 2011. These metrics appear to reflect institutional performance or ranking scores, with values ranging from 96.0 to 71.7.

The California Institute of Technology achieved the highest recorded value at 96.0, followed closely by the Massachusetts Institute of Technology at 95.6. Johns Hopkins University recorded 86.4, while the University of Toronto measured 82.0. Carnegie Mellon University's metric stood at 79.3, with the University of British Columbia at 73.8. The University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign recorded 73.0, and McGill University completed the dataset with a value of 71.7.

These 2011 metrics collectively document a comparative assessment of these institutions' performance during that year, with the values suggesting a hierarchical ranking among these prominent universities in research and academic excellence.&lt;SEP&gt;A recorded value of 73.8 for University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill in 2011.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-585fbbf6faaf2d2005a7bb512789db5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ad99513f675fcaa96dc1cf730c88323a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-897b58651fa54b4798c190adf306f8b6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e815538d0826e826b391f3bedbae20da&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0bfe3b23de589d658a534f6af0a06c88&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-977dfd7e17dbcb3c76b9c6972c954be3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eabcde21ef4b9fdbad73cfcf72eb5448&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-280a7ae0fb8ad42364816f57c91af9e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eecbe57db1438e971999c19f4e1cc992</data>
