<node id="2013 Metric">
  <data key="d0">2013 Metric</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The 2013 Metric represents a performance measurement recorded across eight leading North American research institutions during 2013. California Institute of Technology achieved the highest recorded value at 95.5, followed by Massachusetts Institute of Technology at 93.1. Johns Hopkins University recorded 85.6, while University of Toronto measured 82.2. Carnegie Mellon University registered 81.5, with University of British Columbia at 77.3. University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign and McGill University completed the dataset with values of 75.8 and 75.7 respectively. These metrics collectively reflect the comparative performance standings of these institutions during the 2013 measurement period.&lt;SEP&gt;A recorded value of 72.4 for University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill in 2013.</data>
