<node id="2014 Metric">
  <data key="d0">2014 Metric</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The 2014 Metric represents a set of performance measurements recorded across eight prominent North American research institutions during 2014. These metrics appear to reflect institutional rankings or assessments based on research output, academic reputation, or similar evaluative criteria.

California Institute of Technology achieved the highest recorded value at 94.9, followed by Massachusetts Institute of Technology at 93.0. Johns Hopkins University recorded 83.7, while University of Toronto measured 78.3. Carnegie Mellon University registered 76.0, and University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign recorded 71.4. University of British Columbia achieved 70.8, with McGill University recording the lowest value among the institutions at 68.1.

The 2014 Metric data demonstrates a clear hierarchical distribution across these institutions, with scores ranging from 94.9 to 68.1, suggesting differentiated performance levels or standings within the measured category during that year.&lt;SEP&gt;A recorded value of 64.5 for University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill in 2014.</data>
