<node id="2015 Metric">
  <data key="d0">2015 Metric</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The 2015 Metric represents a performance measurement recorded across eight leading North American research institutions during 2015. California Institute of Technology achieved the highest recorded value at 94.3, followed by Massachusetts Institute of Technology at 91.9. Johns Hopkins University recorded 83.0, while University of Toronto measured 79.3. Carnegie Mellon University registered 74.3, with University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign at 71.9 and University of British Columbia at 71.8. McGill University recorded the lowest value among the institutions at 69.6.

These metrics collectively document a comparative assessment of these institutions in 2015, with scores ranging from 69.6 to 94.3, reflecting relative performance or ranking differences across the measured institutions during that year.&lt;SEP&gt;A recorded value of 65.9 for University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill in 2015.</data>
