<node id="2016 Metric">
  <data key="d0">2016 Metric</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The 2016 Metric represents a performance measurement recorded across eight leading North American research institutions during 2016. California Institute of Technology achieved the highest recorded value at 95.2, followed by Massachusetts Institute of Technology at 92.0. Johns Hopkins University recorded 87.6, while University of Toronto measured 83.9. Carnegie Mellon University registered 82.3, with University of British Columbia at 75.3. University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign recorded 74.5, and McGill University completed the dataset at 72.6. These metrics collectively document comparative performance assessments across these institutions during the 2016 calendar year, with values ranging from 72.6 to 95.2.&lt;SEP&gt;A recorded value of 66.4 for University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill in 2016.</data>
