<node id="2013">
  <data key="d0">2013</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">2013 is a year for which metric values were recorded across multiple prominent universities worldwide. Stanford University recorded the highest value at 93.7, followed by Princeton University at 92.7. University of California, Los Angeles and Columbia University recorded values of 87.7 and 87.0 respectively, while University of Pennsylvania recorded 86.6. Northwestern University and University of Michigan recorded values of 83.1 and 82.6 respectively.

Additional institutions recorded the following metric values in 2013: Georgia Institute of Technology at 78.8, University of Tokyo at 78.3, National University of Singapore at 77.5, New York University at 72.8, University of California, Santa Barbara at 75.6, University of Hong Kong at 75.6, University of California, San Diego at 75.2, and Karolinska Institute at 72.4.&lt;SEP&gt;2013 represents a year with a recorded metric value of 73.1 for London School of Economics and Political Science.&lt;SEP&gt;2013 represents a year in which Australian National University recorded a metric value of 75.4.&lt;SEP&gt;Year 2013 with an associated metric value of 70.7 for Peking University.&lt;SEP&gt;2013 represents a year with a recorded value of 71.8 for University of California, Davis.&lt;SEP&gt;Year 2013 with a recorded value of 68.9 for Brown University.</data>
