<node id="2014">
  <data key="d0">2014</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">2014 is a temporal data point characterized by recorded metric values across a diverse set of international universities. Stanford University achieved the highest value at 93.8, followed by Princeton University at 92.7. University of California, Los Angeles reported 86.3, while Columbia University recorded 85.2. University of Pennsylvania documented 81.0, University of Michigan 79.2, and Northwestern University 77.1. University of Tokyo, the only non-U.S. institution among the top performers, recorded 76.4.

Additional institutions recorded the following values for 2014: Georgia Institute of Technology at 71.6, National University of Singapore at 72.4, University of California, Santa Barbara at 68.4, Karolinska Institute at 67.8, University of California, San Diego at 67.4, and New York University at 67.4. University of Hong Kong recorded a metric value of 65.3 for the same year.&lt;SEP&gt;2014 represents a year with a recorded metric value of 69.8 for London School of Economics and Political Science.&lt;SEP&gt;2014 represents a year in which Australian National University recorded a metric value of 64.4.&lt;SEP&gt;Year 2014 with an associated metric value of 65.0 for Peking University.&lt;SEP&gt;2014 represents a year with a recorded value of 63.2 for University of California, Davis.&lt;SEP&gt;Year 2014 with a recorded value of 63.2 for Brown University.</data>
