<node id="Performance Metrics">
  <data key="d0">Performance Metrics</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Performance Metrics represent a comprehensive dataset of numerical scores assigned to eight leading international universities over a six-year period from 2011 to 2016. These metrics provide a quantitative assessment of institutional performance across this timeframe.

Harvard University achieved the highest performance scores among the institutions tracked, with metrics ranging from 91.6 to 96.1. Imperial College London followed with scores between 87.5 and 90.7, while the University of Chicago recorded metrics ranging from 86.9 to 90.4. ETH Zurich demonstrated performance scores between 83.4 and 88.3 across the same period.

The University of Melbourne's performance metrics ranged from 68.2 to 77.9, while École Polytechnique Fédérale de Lausanne recorded values between 66.3 and 76.1. LMU Munich showed metrics spanning from 63.0 to 77.3 over the six-year interval. King's College London exhibited the widest relative growth trajectory, with performance metrics increasing from 59.7 in 2011 to 78.2 in 2016.

Collectively, these Performance Metrics illustrate a comparative ranking of institutional excellence, with scores generally trending upward or remaining stable across the 2011-2016 period, reflecting the sustained or improving performance of these prestigious universities during this timeframe.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fd761d2029183293c631f0c4f39b123b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-acff4e65b7895d0f779b67f4959da34f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b4b0879c7c7c5d84029a478ba5949be&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-924e316a97b4f949f979be2d05f8ef5e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8ccef36cc526f6c382444151fba3b19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7cdf6049c6acace06a3396b27d543f7a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f6674b4e5c8a1507da11221fecd644cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9946565d16304c690880ca3101d8694e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
